text: Glamorizing chronic illness... this actually makes me quite sad. Why do we as a society think it's so romantic to be a sick girl? Let me tell you it sucks to be sick and on your death bed. There are no handsome men to save you, there is no beauty in being sick, in feeling like crap all the time. üòû If we are going to talk about chronic illness, let's talk about the realities. The fact that you are in pain all the time, or the fact that you have to take 20 different medications a day, or the fact that you have to struggle for every breath you take. How about the fact that being immunocompromised absolutely sucks, and that we actually could die if we were exposed to dangerous germs. This is no fake crap that is just something to be messed around with and twisted into by Hollywood into a beautiful romantic story. This is sad, and I can't see any reasons that we should keep supporting these kinds of movies. Chronic illness is messy, tragic, and painful. It is not romantic.
